{{Quote|She's a princess. Ask her for a planet.''"<br />"''Or a moon. Two if they are small.|Standro joking around with squadmates [[Dar Keyis]] and [[Isplourrdacartha Estillo|Plour Ilo]]|<ref name="X-Wing Rogue Squadron 23">[[X-Wing Rogue Squadron 23|''X-Wing Rogue Squadron'' 23]]</ref>}}
'''Standro Jcir''' was a [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] from [[Rodia/Legends|Rodia]] who served as an [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] with the [[New Republic Defense Force/Legends|New Republic Defense Force]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], Jcir joined the elite [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] just prior to the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic's]] [[Battle of Brentaal IV (Galactic Civil War)|invasion]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] controlled [[Brentaal system/Legends|Brentaal system]]. During the invasion, Jcir&mdash;flying under the callsign "[[Rogue Twelve]]"&mdash;and his new [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] assisted [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar's]] [[Fleet/Legends|fleet]] in capturing the [[Brentaal Moonbase]], which [[Orbit/Legends|orbited]] the wealthy [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Brentaal IV/Legends|Brentaal IV]]. During the battle for the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] base, Rogue Squadron discovered that Brentaal IV was defended by the Empire's elite [[181st Imperial Fighter Wing/Legends|181st TIE Fighter Wing]]. After the capture of the moon, Rogue Squadron attacked Brentaal IV's [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Vuultin]] to divert Imperial defense resources away from the Republic's true target, the spaceport city of [[Oradin]]. Once Oradin was secure, Rogue Squadron was again sent into Vuultin to prevent the Empire's evacuation of its wealthy citizens. During the intense [[Starfighter combat/Legends|starfighter combat]] of the skirmish, however, Jcir's X-wing was hit by fire from an Imperial [[Anti-aircraft gun|anti-air gun]], causing Jcir's [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] to crash, [[Death/Legends|killing]] the Rodian pilot.

==Biography==
{{Expandsect}}
A [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Rodia/Legends|Rodia]], Standro Jcir served as a [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|T-65 X-wing starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] for the [[New Republic Defense Force/Legends|New Republic Defense Force]] in the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] against the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], six months after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], Jcir was transferred over to the elite [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]]&mdash;under the command of [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]]&mdash;stationed at the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic's]] secret [[Base Delta-Nine]]. Prior to joining the famed [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]], Jcir had fought in thirteen different combat missions for the New Republic. Along with the [[Human/Legends|Humans]] [[Dar Keyis]] and [[Avan Beruss]] and the [[Tunroth]] [[Xarcce Huwla]], Jcir was greeted by Captain Antilles (who was slightly late, having just left debriefing from a past mission) and was introduced to his new squadmates by [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Derek Klivian/Legends|Derek Klivian]].

However, the reason Jcir and the other new Rogues had entered the squadron was because [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]] wanted to raise Rogue Squadron to full strength for the New Republic's planned [[Battle of Brentaal IV (Galactic Civil War)|assault]] on the wealthy Imperial planet [[Brentaal IV/Legends|Brentaal IV]]. Jcir&mdash;given the [[Callsign/Legends|call sign]] "[[Rogue Twelve]]"&mdash;and the rest of Rogue Squadron underwent four weeks worth of intensive flight [[Flight simulator/Legends|holosimulations]] in the span of two weeks to prepare for the upcoming attack on Brentaal.

With their training complete, Rogue Squadron joined the New Republic [[Fleet/Legends|fleet]] under the command of Ackbar&mdash;launching from [[Recopia]]&mdash;in capturing the [[Brentaal Moonbase]] that [[Orbit/Legends|orbited]] Brentaal IV. Jcir and Dar Keyis were two of the battle's casualties.

